location.address: City Point, Ground Floor, Dhole Patil Road, Pune

review.review_text: It was a great experience at Asia Kitchen by Mainland China. Not the just the food but also the ambience was spectacular. I would definitely visit their outlet in Mumbai again to enjoy the experience

Visited this place on the occasion of Clay Pot Festival. This place is located in the center of the city at one of the prime locations in Pune.  I was invited to food tasting and this tasting was far different from the other tasting I go, Clay Pot Festival was a great all the dish served by the restaurant was amazing in all the way.   Coming to Food I tasted -  **Sushi** 1. Cream Cheese Avocado  - This was coated with cream cheese and white rice, I just loved this Sushi it was too delicious.   2. Blue Rice Sushi - This was coated with blue rice and it was also good but comparatively like the cheese cream once.    **Dimsums**   1. Truffle Infused Edamame Dumpling   2. Chicken Pakchoy wrap with Sichuan Broth   **Appetizers**   1. Babycorn with Barbequed Onion  - This dish was delicious and was made with fresh vegetable baby corn and Barbeque onion made this dish yummy  **Mains**   1. Buddha's Delight in a Casserole   - The casserole dish was too good and served in Clay Pot, it was made with vegetable and it gives a real taste of Asia dish.  2. Sapo Vegetables  - Made with all fresh veggies this dish was health as half cooked and give a real taste of vegetables. 3. Sanpei Chicken  -   - I love the chicken with chili it was perfect and It was giving me a fragrance of clay which made this dish more delicious. 4. Malaysian Fish Curry in a Clay Pot  - Malaysian fish was good in taste and clay poy smells were coming from the dish, I just love the dish. 5. Shredded Duck with Mango in a Clay Pot - Shredded Duck was dam good, I just love the dish because they prepared it so well. 6. Asian Greens Clay Pot Rice    **Desserts**   Mango Pudding  - I love this mango Pudding and the way they served it, Mint leaf on the top was amazing. Coconut Dumpling with Date Syrup - It was steam fried and love the dumpling of coconut.  Mocktails and Cocktail were also amazing.  This is an amazing time to visit with your family and friends....

Visited this place for lunch on Sunday. Over restaurant was fully occupied but since we had reservation we managed to get a table quickly. To start with, Food tasted Indo Chinese. Quantity was less compare to the price tag so 1 point less for that. 1 point less for serving food cold and it looked like it was already cooked just decorated the plate and served. I must say food tasted really good so over all good experience

Have your tried #ClayPotFestival @asiaKitchen.  Around 14 dishes are being served in Clay pots, just like the good old school days. Join Asia kitchen on an epicurean fare of rich and traditional Asian Clay Pot delicacies.  Vegetarian 🌱  Sichuan Vegetable in Clay pot  Sapo Vegetable  Three cup Assorted Vegetables in a Clay pot.  Buddha’s delight casserole  Sizzling Eggplant  Rice & Noodles 🍝  Asian green Clay pot  Chicken Clay pot rice  Ginger noodles in casserole This was my first time with complete authentic Chinese food, and it was amazing. The food is sumptuous, that you will be amazed. The sushi and dim sums were garnished beautifully and tasted good.  I loved the Sichuan Vegetable in Clay pot and ginger Noodles in casserole. I don’t remember the name of desserts but one was      Mango Pudding and other was small dumplings in shape of modak with coconut filling inside. Both of these items were 5/5.   Not to miss, their range of cocktails was astonishing 👌.   Their staff is so polite, attentive and alert. A huge appreciation to staff 👏🏻 .  For someone like me, who has never experienced Asian cuisine, this place stunned me!.  Make sure you visit Asia Kitchen and Enjoy before the Clay pot festival ends.

I guess this place is simply over rated going by zomato reviews.  Had been there for lunch and this place on a Sunday afternoon was almost empty. Food was just okay, I feel most of it was stale.  Well Chinese food is supposed to be cooked fresh with a burst of flavours and served hot. This was certainly missing.

review.review_text: I ordered food from here and was not impressed at all. It wasn’t worth the hype and restaurant did not even pick up when I tried to connect.  - Water chestnut and chive dimsums were ok. Nothing new or worth the ‘best seller’ tag  - Edamame petit poi’s and truffle oil had a dense paste like filling and did not taste good  - Mapo Tofu was a big disappointment again. It had a lot of mushrooms with no overall taste. It had a small portion size with no rice

Undoubtedly the best sushi outlet in Pune, although I’ve eaten better otherwise. The tender and succulent goodness of the sushi is what makes you go there again and again and again. Been here 4 times already and their dynamite prawn sushi and edamame dumplings have been a hot favourite 😍 . Price wise it’s perfect for the quantity served.
Really nice restaurant at phoenix.  We enjoy alot going there and trying something new each time.  Everything taste good and the fish tastes fresh

Amazing food ❤️  Visited here on a quiet Tuesday evening and we were seated right away. The ambience is decent and comfortable. About the food, we ordered:  1) Vegetable Chui Chow Dimsums: (5/5) Really really good! The filling was perfect and they tasted great. 2) Avacado Salad Maki: (5/5) only if I could rate this more than 5/5 I would! Amazing flavours ❤️ The ginger and wasabi sides provide a great hit. 3) Vietnamese Pho: (3/5) This wasn't great though. The preparation was perfect but it tasted bland to be honest. Would've been happy with aore flavourful broth. 4) Chilly Garlic Noodles: (5/5) Wow wow wow. Bang on spicy and amazing ❤️  Overall, it was an incredible food experience! Do visit if you love Asian cuisine.

Ambience - 2 stars. One, water was dripping from the ceiling right behind our table. Two, the layout is such that people can walk across the restaurant to go from inside of the mall to the outside (or vice versa). Is it a restaurant within a mall or the other way around?  Service - 2 stars. 1. A waiter walks up to us and tells us, " I'll be waiting for you tonight" . Great! A personalized dining experience...is what we thought we'd get. But we didn't. The waiter was all around the place waiting for several other tables just like any other budget restaurant. ( This isn't a budget restaurant by any means though). Had to try desperately to get his attention a few times. We had at least 2 other waiters come by our table to take orders. Even the Manager ( it looked like him) came by our table. They look confused. Unorganized.  2. Besides the quality and quantity of food, what really puts any diner off is the restaurant telling them that the food they want is unavailable. What makes it even worse is them telling this to us several minutes after taking the order! This is exactly what happened with us. After going through their exhaustive list of menu, we decided to order a particular style of salad. The waiter takes the order. We are looking forward to tasting something new. Several minutes later, the waiter returns and tells us that the main ingredient itself of the salad isn't available. What a shame! If it's not available, mention it in your menu! Or at least make your waiters aware!  Food - 2 stars. Ordered a style of fried fish for starters. It was covered with tons of flour and was excessively oily. Not good at all. The noodles that we ordered tasted good. I must give this to them. But again, it was way too oily. Had two different styles of dimsums which tasted just fine. But the quantity was meagre, to put it politely. Which brings me to the final segment...  Price - 2 stars. Now it doesn't matter if I'm super rich or super poor. I've come to your restaurant to get your services for which I'm paying. And I want the worth of every penny I'm spending, back. Just four pcs of dimsums for well over 400 rupees? A 100 bucks for just 1 dimsum? Are you joking? It is not even a Michelin rated restaurant nor is the service upto the mark. Totally unfair and unjust pricing.  Also, we ordered a ginger ale from their bar menu. Was expecting something original coming off their bar which was right next to our table. But what we got was a glass full of ice and a can of Schweppes Ginger Ale! Are you absolutely kidding us??  Won't be coming back here nor going to recommend anybody unless at least a couple of the above mentioned concerns are dealt with.

review.review_text: Tried this place for weekends and I can def say this is not ideal because of their quality of food preparation. Wait time was superficial. Food quality was absurd. Def not recommended.

My all time favourite for Chinese destination. There are so many varieties which might always confuse us what to eat and what not! Best part, taste is available as per spicy you wanted or gravy you need as thick. Best to taste on souls, non veg starters.

Chang's the favorite restaurant for Chinese food.They have varieties of menu for veg and non-veg.Recently we had a dinner at Chang's and the must try out dishes from the menu are Chicken manchow soup, Chang's special veg noodles, Veg Manchurian,Minced Chicken chilly rice.We just loved this place.  Follow us on Instagram: @the_crazy_indian_chef

Good Chinese food at a decent price point. A lot of their dishes come with their own gravies so that's something that is better confirmed before ordering noodles and a main course dish. As a side note, their American chopsuey is highly recommended.
Attitude of the staff is not good . food is good but at the time of availing zomato good benefits they will treat you differently.everything else is ok.

The food was excellent and the best part was the service provided by our stewart, Biswajeet. Will be looking forward to come again, and try more dishes

We had the spicy tamyam chicken soup, burnt garlic chilli chicken starter and the burnt garlic chkn fried rice and i must say that it didnt fail to leave us impressed. The overall food quality was great as well as the quantity. For the pricing, it seems moderately expensive. The ambience was good if not great i'd say but the staff was really friendly. So yeah...highly recommended!!

Good chinesse food...the service was prompt and food quality was great. They also reconmended us to try out their speaciality items which were great as well.
This place in Koregaon park has amazing food. A must go to chinese place. The noodles are amazing. The staff is really courteous and the has a great variety of food.
